.TH "batadv_tt_check_roam_count" 9 "batadv_tt_check_roam_count" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
batadv_tt_check_roam_count \- check if a client has roamed too frequently
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" batadv_tt_check_roam_count
.BI "(struct batadv_priv *bat_priv "  ","
.BI "u8 *client "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bat_priv" 12
the bat priv with all the soft interface information
.IP "client" 12
mac address of the roaming client
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function checks whether the client already reached the
maximum number of possible roaming phases. In this case the ROAMING_ADV
will not be sent.
.SH "RETURN"
true if the ROAMING_ADV can be sent, false otherwise
